author: Jessica Durando
title: Elephant joins family during brunch in Zimbabwe
text:
Elephant joins family during brunch in Zimbabwe USA Today 2 days ago Jessica Durando
© Provided by USA Today Hold on to your brunch!
Shane Wolf of California says his family had a "close encounter" while he was on safari in Zimbabwe, according to an Instagram post this week.
They were having brunch in Mana Pools, according to Wolf, when an elephant interrupted.
"The young bull got a little surprised when it saw us, as they have bad eyesight," Wolf said. "Luckily nobody was hurt and the staff did an amazing job scaring the elephant away."
As far as his opinion on elephants after the situation, "I love these amazing animals and still do, the land is theirs and we must respect this."
